cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the transferability of adversarial examples between different deep learning models, which is a common topic in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the security implications of adversarial examples, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Lastly, the paper proposes a modification to existing training setups, which could be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
